Customize the Enter or Return Key in Messaging for Web

By default, Messaging for Web is configured so that the Enter or Return key sends a message. To make it start a new line of text instead, change the deployment settings.

This article applies to:	Messaging for Web channels

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up this feature:	
Customize Application 
AND Modify Metadata Through Metadata API Functions

Select Embedded Service Deployments from Setup.
Click Edit Settings.
Select Press Enter or Return to start a new line of text. To use the Enter or Return key to send a message, deselect the checkbox.
Save your changes.

When the Enter or Return button is set to send a message, start a new line of text by pressing Option + (Enter or Return) (Mac) or Alt + (Enter or Return) (Windows). When the Enter or Return button is set to start a new line of text, send a message by pressing Option + (Enter or Return) (Mac) or Alt + (Enter or Return) (Windows).
title: Customizing Messaging for Web in Service Cloud
